									<div class="post_tag"><i class="fa fa-tags"></i><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/american-foreign-policy/" rel="tag">American foreign policy</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/casey-michel/" rel="tag">Casey Michel</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/corruption/" rel="tag">corruption</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/dark-money/" rel="tag">Dark Money</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/foreign-agents-how-american-lobbyists-and-lawmakers-threaten-democracy-around-the-world/" rel="tag">Foreign Agents: How American Lobbyists and Lawmakers Threaten Democracy Around the World</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/foreign-policy/" rel="tag">foreign policy</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/lobbying/" rel="tag">lobbying</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/lobbyists/" rel="tag">lobbyists</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/macmillan/" rel="tag">Macmillan</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/st-martins-press/" rel="tag">St. Martin's Press</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/washington-d-c/" rel="tag">Washington D.C.</a></div>									
																		
